<Primary>
<PrimaryPrelims>
<Title><?start-line?>A
<?new-line?>Bill

<?new-line?>To
</Title>
<Number /><LongTitle><?start-line?><Para>
<Text>Make provision for the parents of young offenders to be legally responsible for <?new-line?>their actions.<DateOfEnactment><DateText /></DateOfEnactment>
</Text>
</Para>
</LongTitle>
<DateOfEnactment><DateText /></DateOfEnactment>
<PrimaryPreamble>
<EnactingText>
<Para>
<Text>B<SmallCaps>e it enacted</SmallCaps> by the Queen’s most Excellent Majesty, by and with the advice and <?new-line?>consent of the Lords Spiritual and Temporal, and Commons, in this present <?new-line?>Parliament assembled, and by the authority of the same, as follows:—</Text>
</Para>
</EnactingText>
</PrimaryPreamble>
</PrimaryPrelims>
<Body NumberFormat="default">
<P1group id="p00001">
<Title><?start-line?>Parental Responsibility</Title>
<P1>
<Pnumber>1</Pnumber>
<P1para>
<P2>
<Pnumber>1</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>A person commits an offence if a child or young person for whom they have <?new-line?>parental responsibility commits an offence but is not charged or subjected to a <?new-line?>penalty.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
<P2>
<Pnumber>2</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>A person guilty of an offence under subsection (1) shall be liable to the same <?new-line?>charge or penalty as is specified in law for the offence commited by the young <?new-line?>person.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
<P2>
<Pnumber>3</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>In this section—</Text>
<UnorderedList Decoration="none" Class="Definition">
<ListItem>
<Para>
<Text><?start-line?>“child” has the meaning given by Section 99 of the Criminal Justice Act <?new-line?>1991,</Text>
</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>
<Text><?start-line?>“parental responsibility” has the meaning given by Section 3 of the <?new-line?>Children Act 1989,</Text>
</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>
<Text><?start-line?>“young person” has the meaning given by Section 99 of the Criminal <?new-line?>Justice Act 1991.</Text>
</Para>
</ListItem>
</UnorderedList>
</P2para>
</P2>
</P1para>
</P1>
</P1group>
<P1group id="p00002">
<Title><?start-line?>Short Title, Commencement and Extent</Title>
<P1>
<Pnumber>2</Pnumber>
<P1para>
<P2>
<Pnumber>1</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>This Act may be cited as the Young Offenders (Parental Responsibility) Act <?new-line?>2013.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
<P2>
<Pnumber>2</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>This Act shall come into force on such day as the Secretary of State may by <?new-line?>order made by statutory instrument appoint.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
<P2>
<Pnumber>3</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>This Act extends to England and Wales only.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
</P1para>
</P1>
</P1group>
